Vice President Harris spoke with Department of Homeland Security Secretary Alejandro Mayorkas regarding his trip to Del Rio. She expressed her concerns about the mistreatment of Haitian migrants by border patrol agents on horses and emphasized the importance of treating people with dignity and in accordance with the law. Secretary Mayorkas shared the Vice President's concerns and mentioned that he would update her on the investigation by the Office of Professional Responsibility. Additionally, they discussed the efforts being made by the Department of Homeland Security to address the humanitarian needs of individuals at the border, including providing food, shelter, clothing, and medical care, as well as collaborating with non-governmental and international organizations. The Vice President acknowledged Secretary Mayorkas' concerns and expressed her intention to follow up on the matter in the near future.